        <methods>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <section>
                        <title>Grid generation</title>
                        <para>The aspect grid was generated using the previsouly created 30 meter
                            DEM (dem30_utm) in ArcInfo's grid function. Values in the grid were
                            converted from floating point to integer format and value attribute
                            table (.vat) was built. Although the original values are truncated, the
                            accuray is not significantly affected. Aspect identifies the down-slope
                            direction of the maximum rate of change in elevation from each cell to
                            its neighbors. The values of the resulting grid are the compass
                            direction of the aspect expressed in positive degrees from 0 to 360 and
                            measured clockwise from the north. Cells in the input grid of zero slope
                            (flat) are assigned an value of -1.</para>
                    </section>
                </description>
